      <img src="/mbbwimages/metalwork.jpg" align="right"><span class="maintext">

<h1>Metal Work</h1>

<ol type=1><p>

<li>Show the divisions of a foot, a meter, and a centimeter.<p>

<li>Show how to make common joints and seams in a sheet metal, such as lap.<p>

<li>Use tin cans to make two useful things that need cutting, bending, and edging.<p>

<li>Show how to use the following tools: soldering copper, iron file, ball peen hammer, tinner's snips, pliers, hacksaw, blow torch, and hand drill.<p>

<li>Do the following:
<ol type=a>
<li>Draw working sketches of a cake pan and a funnel.
<li>Make patterns based on the working sketches you made.</ol><p>

<li>Make any of the following articles by sawing, filing, riveting, and/or drilling: wire hangers, frames of a lamp shade, hinges, candle stand, caliper, paper weight, bird cage, wire waste basket, dish rack, wire wall planter, soap dish, wire decors, garden trowel, spoon, tray, soup ladle, etc.</ol>


</span><p>    </td>
